==English==
===Etymology===
From the Nguni group of languages ''khaya'': home.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪə|-eɪə]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''khaya'''|'''khayas'''}}
#(Properly) A native house or hut.
#(used loosely) Servant's quarters separated from the main house.
#{{Slang}} Anyone's house or home.
